s%20also%20clear%20that%20we%20differ%20on%20the%20strategic%20direction%20for%20the%20Company%20going%20forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222982%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%2223andMe%20CEO%20Anne%20Wojcicki%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ee782e5f34d05700a0bf1d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221991%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnne%20Wojcicki%20is%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%2023andMe.%20%3Cp%3ESteve%20Jennings%2FGetty%20Images%2FTechCrunch%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20that%20despite%20earning%20%24299%20million%20in%20revenue%20in%202023%20and%20%24219%20million%20in%202024%2C%20the%20company%20never%20made%20a%20profit.%20Its%20stock%20price%20peaked%20in%20February%202021%20but%20has%20steadily%20declined%20since%2C%20reaching%20an%20all-time%20low%20of%2029%20cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E23andMe's%20reputation%20took%20a%20further%20hit%20with%20consumers%20in%20September%20when%20Wojcicki%20said%20in%20an%20SEC%20filing%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bconsidering%20third%20party%20takeover%20proposals.%26quot%3B%20She%20walked%20back%20that%20statement%20later%20that%20month%20in%20a%20separate%20filing%2C%20but%20the%20damage%20was%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutlets%20like%20The%20Atlantic%20reported%20that%20Wojcicki's%20potential%20sale%20of%2023andMe%20could%20also%20mean%20the%20sale%20of%20user%20data.%20The%20director%20of%20cybersecurity%20at%20Electronic%20Frontier%20Foundation%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20focused%20on%20digital%20privacy%2C%20urged%20their%20186%2C000%20X%20followers%20to%20delete%20their%20data%20from%2023andMe.%20That%20post%20garnered%20more%20than%20531%2C000%20views%20in%20three%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20X%20post%20touched%20on%20concerns%20plaguing%20the%20DNA%20test%20kit%20industry%3A%20Your%20private%20DNA%20data%20may%20not%20stay%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BData%20is%20data%20%E2%80%94%20once%20it's%20out%20there%2C%20it's%20very%20hard%20to%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivacy-security-risks-genetic-testing-23andme-ancestry-dna-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJames%20Hazel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20biomedical%20researcher%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E23andMe%20says%20the%20personal%20data%20it%20collects%20includes%20registration%20information%20like%20birth%20date%2C%20genetic%20information%20like%20a%20user's%20genotype%2C%20sample%20information%20like%20saliva%2C%20and%20self-reported%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeyond%20our%20contracted%20laboratory%2C%20with%20which%20we%20work%20to%20process%20a%20customer's%20sample%20and%20deliver%20their%20results%2C%20customer%20information%20will%20not%20be%20shared%20with%20any%20other%20entity%20unless%20they%20provide%20us%20with%20consent%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20a%2023andMe%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20doesn't%20share%20data%20with%20%26quot%3Bemployers%2C%20insurance%20companies%2C%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20or%20any%20public%20databases.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22412bbc19-4bef-4532-9c97-39228ce572c0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20how%20to%20ask%2023andMe%20to%20delete%20your%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsers%20who%20want%20their%20personal%20information%20removed%20from%2023andMe%20can%20opt-out%20in%20the%20%26quot%3B23andMe%20Data%26quot%3B%20section%20in%20Account%20Settings.%20But%2023andMe%20says%20it%20is%20legally%20required%20to%20retain%20some%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20will%20delete%20the%20majority%20of%20your%20Personal%20Information%2C%20we%20are%20required%20to%20retain%20some%20information%20to%20comply%20with%20our%20legal%20obligation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20website%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B23andMe%20and%2For%20our%20contracted%20genotyping%20laboratory%20will%20retain%20your%20Genetic%20Information%2C%20date%20of%20birth%2C%20and%20sex%20as%20required%20for%20compliance%20with%20applicable%20legal%20obligations...%20even%20if%20you%20chose%20to%20delete%20your%20account%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20privacy%20statement%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20privacy%20statement%20says%2023andMe%20will%20also%20retain%20some%20information%20associated%20with%20user%20accounts%2C%20like%20email%20addresses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20users%20who%20participated%20in%2023andMe%20Research%2C%20their%20genetic%20data%20and%20self-reported%20information%20won't%20be%20used%20in%20future%20research%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCustomers%20always%20have%20the%20option%20to%20delete%20their%20account%20at%20any%20time%2C%20and%20once%20the%20request%20is%20confirmed%2C%20we%20will%20immediately%20and%20automatically%20begin%20the%20deletion%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BDeleting%20an%20account%20and%20associated%20data%20will%20permanently%20delete%20the%20data%20associated%20with%20all%20profiles%20within%20the%20account.%20If%20a%20customer%20asks%20us%20to%20store%20their%20genetic%20samples%2C%20they%20will%20be%20discarded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-delete-your-23andme-data-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728248806000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67017528198738e3a70e89da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-delete-your-23andme-data-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2223andMe's%20once%20rising%20star%20has%20dimmed%20amid%20a%20series%20of%20setbacks%2C%20leading%20some%20users%20to%20wonder%20what%20will%20happen%20to%20their%20genetic%20data.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40businessinsider.com%20(Lauren%20Edmonds)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%