%20However%2C%20Kajol%20accepted%20the%20role%2C%20and%20Aishwarya%20later%20mentioned%20that%20the%20character%20had%20changed%20from%20the%20initial%20narration%20she%20received.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fnot-kajol-aishwarya-rai-was-karan-johars-first-choice-for-anjalis-role-in-kabhi-khushi-kabhie-gham%2Farticleshow%2F113991642.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWouldn't%20Have%20Given%20Birth...%26quot%3B%3A%20Gaza%20Mothers%20Struggle%20To%20Care%20For%20Newborns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGazan%20mother%20Rana%20Salah%20cradles%20her%20one-month-old%20daughter%20Milana%20in%20her%20arms%20in%20a%20sweltering%20tent%20for%20the%20displaced%2C%20and%20speaks%20of%20the%20guilt%20she%20feels%20for%20bringing%20her%20child%20into%20a%20world%20of%20war%20and%20suffering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20were%20up%20to%20me%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20gotten%20pregnant%20or%20given%20birth%20during%20the%20war%20because%20life%20is%20completely%20different%3B%20we've%20never%20lived%20this%20life%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20speaking%20at%20a%20camp%20in%20Deir%20al-Balah%20in%20the%20central%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20gave%20birth%20twice%20before%2C%20and%20life%20was%20better%20and%20easier%20for%20me%20and%20the%20child.%20Now%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I've%20wronged%20both%20myself%20and%20the%20child%20because%20we%20deserve%20to%20live%20better%20than%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilana%20was%20born%20in%20a%20hospital%20tent%20by%20caesarean%20owing%20to%20complications%20with%20Salah's%20pregnancy.%20The%20family%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20return%20home%20due%20to%20the%20conflict%2C%20moving%20instead%20from%20one%20tent%20to%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilana%20is%20one%20of%20around%2020%2C000%20babies%20to%20have%20been%20born%20in%20Gaza%20in%20the%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20UNICEF%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20war%2C%20a%20particularly%20deadly%20episode%20in%20the%20decades-old%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20was%20triggered%20on%20October%207%2C%202023%2C%20when%20Hamas%20militants%20attacked%20Israel%2C%20killing%201%2C200%20people%20and%20taking%20about%20250%20hostages%2C%20according%20to%20Israeli%20tallies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20air%20and%20artillery%20strikes%20in%20response%20have%20reduced%20much%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20enclave%20to%20rubble%20and%20more%20than%2041%2C500%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20Israeli%20assault%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Gaza%20health%20ministry.%20Most%20of%20Gaza's%202.3%20million%20residents%20have%20been%20displaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EINFECTION%20RISK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESalah%20fans%20Milana%20with%20cardboard%20and%20says%20the%20heat%20is%20bad%20for%20the%20baby's%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20returning%20to%20our%20house%2C%20we%20keep%20moving%20from%20one%20tent%20to%20another...%20where%20diseases%20are%20widespread%20and%20the%20water%20is%20contaminated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20has%20said%20postnatal%20services%20have%20decreased%20significantly%20in%20Gaza%2C%20so%20women%20who%20have%20complications%20have%20less%20access%20to%20the%20care%20they%20need%2C%20as%20do%20their%20babies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERick%20Brennan%2C%20the%20WHO's%20Eastern%20Mediterranean%20Regional%20emergency%20director%2C%20said%20malnutrition%20was%20a%20threat%20to%20newborns%2C%20particularly%20if%20their%20mothers%20were%20unable%20to%20breastfeed%2C%20as%20there%20was%20no%20access%20to%20breast%20milk%20substitutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisplacement%20and%20being%20constantly%20on%20the%20move%20are%20disruptive%20for%20a%20newborn%20and%20expose%20them%20to%20risks%20of%20infection%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManar%20Abu%20Jarad%20is%20staying%20in%20a%20school%20shelter%20run%20by%20the%20UN%20Palestinian%20refugee%20agency%20(UNRWA).%20Her%20youngest%20daughter%20Sahar%20was%20born%20on%20Sept.%204th%2C%20also%20by%20caesarean%20section.%20Her%20husband%20was%20killed%20in%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20hearing%20she%20would%20need%20a%20caesarean%20for%20the%20birth%2C%20she%20worried%20about%20how%20she%20would%20care%20for%20her%20other%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20already%20have%20three%20girls.%20I%20started%20shouting...%20How%20can%20I%20carry%20(water)%20buckets%3F%20How%20can%20I%20bathe%20my%20daughters%3F%20How%20can%20I%20help%20them%20and%20my%20husband%20is%20not%20with%20me%2C%20he%20was%20martyred.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildren%20rock%20baby%20Sahar%2C%20who%20is%20swaddled%20in%20a%20crib%2C%20next%20to%20Jarad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20reached%20the%20point%20where%20I%20cannot%20carry%20the%20responsibility%20for%20this%20girl%20...%20Thank%20God%20I%20found%20some%20help%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20has%20borrowed%20what%20she%20can%20from%20family%20and%20uses%20one%20diaper%20a%20day%20for%20the%20baby%20as%20she%20can't%20afford%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20the%20money%20to%20provide%20diapers%20or%20milk%20for%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJarad%20longs%20for%20an%20end%20to%20the%20war%20and%20a%20return%20to%20her%20home%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20just%20a%20tent%20next%20to%20her%20former%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20go%20home.%20Enough%20of%20all%20the%20exhaustion%20we%20are%20experiencing%20here%2C%20enough%20carrying%20buckets%2C%20enough%20of%20the%20dirt%20in%20the%20bathrooms.%20It's%20really%2C%20really%20hard%20and%20really%20tiring%20for%20us.%20Diseases%20are%20everywhere.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3