%5C%22wp-image-234723%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22693%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%20(Image%20courtesy%20Wikimedia%20Commons)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFateh%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20conservation%20was%20marked%20by%20his%20incredible%20knowledge%20of%20the%20terrain%20inside%20Ranthambore%E2%80%99s%20core%20area%20and%20the%20depth%20of%20his%20engagement%20with%20the%20local%20community%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20was%20relocating%2016%20villages%20inhabited%20in%20the%20core%20area%20of%20the%20National%20Park%20and%20ensuring%20that%20the%20village%20economy%20thrived%20despite%20this%20resettlement%20and%20a%20crackdown%20on%20poaching.%20He%20nearly%20died%20for%20his%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20as%20a%20forest%20officer%2C%20his%20loyalties%20only%20lay%20with%20the%20forests%20and%20not%20politicians%20or%20superior%20officers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20feature%20of%20his%20work%20that%20would%20come%20at%20a%20great%20personal%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Jamal%20Ara%3A%20The%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20when%20the%20field%20of%20ornithology%20was%20dominated%20by%20men%2C%20Jamal%20Ara%20stood%20out%20as%20a%20pioneer.%20It%20was%20the%20legendary%20ornithologist%20Salim%20Ali%20who%20called%20her%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20present-day%20Jharkhand%2C%20her%20work%20on%20the%20ornithology%20of%20the%20Chota%20Nagpur%20plateau%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20the%20only%20comprehensive%20study%20of%20birds%20in%20the%20region%20till%20date%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20an%20essay%20by%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20titled%20%3Cem%3EThe%20First%20Lady%20of%20Indian%20Ornithology%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20published%20in%20a%20recent%20collection%20of%20essays%20titled%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FWOMEN-WILD-Brilliant-Wildlife-Biologists%2Fdp%2F9353451817%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWomen%20in%20the%20Wild%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Eedited%20by%20Anita%20Mani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20only%20studying%20till%20Class%2010%2C%20she%20was%20a%20prolific%20writer%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20birds.%20According%20to%20Kazmi%2C%20from%201949%20to%201988%2C%20she%20contributed%20to%20more%20than%2060%20papers%20and%20published%20articles%20to%20journals%20including%20the%20Bombay%20Natural%20History%20Society%20and%20Bengal%20Natural%20History%20Society%2C%20and%20the%20Newsletter%20for%20Birdwatchers%2C%20a%20publication%20read%20by%20amateur%20and%20professional%20ornithologists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20a%20small%20booklet%20for%20children%20titled%20%3Cem%3EWatching%20Birds%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20by%20the%20National%20Book%20Trust%20(NBT).%20The%20book%20is%20currently%20in%20its%2013th%20edition%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20educate%20children%20on%20the%20birds%20of%20India%20in%20multiple%20languages%20till%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20her%20prolific%20writing%2C%20she%20also%20raised%20awareness%20among%20the%20masses%20through%20her%20programmes%20in%20All%20India%20Radio%20(AIR)%20and%20also%20dabbled%20in%20journalism%20for%20mainstream%20publication.%20%E2%80%9CMore%20importantly%2C%20in%20those%20days%2C%20she%20was%20the%20only%20spokesperson%20for%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20imperilled%20wilderness%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20went%20beyond%20just%20advocating%20for%20birds%2C%20according%20to%20Raza.%20Her%20prescriptions%20and%20recommendations%20would%20lay%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20groundwork%20for%20modern%20conservation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Kailash%20Sankhala%3A%20The%20unsung%20hero%20who%20changed%20the%20destiny%20of%20tigers%3C%